<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-876-034  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 876 034.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer  Oct 1989 v22 n10 p71(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Generating applications programs. (Matrix Software's MatrixLayout) (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barr, V.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Matrix Software's Matrix Layout is a set of programs partly aimedat providing users with a Macintosh-like interface, and it bundlesseveral programs: Layout, Paint, HelpMaker, Tutor and Desktop.andO;The $149.95 package seems to be intended for inexperienced users,but they may find it difficult to use.andP;  Layout, the centerpiece ofthe package, allows flowcharts to be converted into executableprograms in several different ways, but lack of documentationhinders use of the program severely.andP;  Paint is used to createpictures for use by programs developed in Layout by drawing themor using clip art; this is the most fun part of the package.andO;Tutor is a 10-minute video that demonstrates use of the package,but it is of limited use because it does not run through asession.andP;  HelpMaker is used to create help screens, and this partof the program works very well.andP;  Desktop is the gateway to all theprograms in the package; it includes a clipboard, notepad,calculator, calendar, clock, font manager and other utilities.andO;Experienced programmers may find Matrix Layout useful for creatinggraphics-based and user-friendly programs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Matrix Software Technology Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Matrix Layout (Program development software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationProgram Development ToolsUtility ProgramsIntegrated software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>